<br>
VI is on record as stating that their objective was to have monks tank worse than rogues. This is problematic in that the only balance reasoning monks had for being defensively superior to them in the first place was that we couldn't deal out the damage they could. That was also on record from VI way back when.<br>
<br>
Now, monks tanking better than warriors was due *only* to VI's fscked up itemization in Velious that allowed monks to jump the 200-300AC we were behind warriors on average at the end of Kunark. If they had done a light tap with the nerfbat, taking 5-10% of monk's mitigation out at all gear levels by changing the AC soft cap it would have solved every issue that was raised, and left class balance intact. However, this is VI, so logic went out the window and they took 31% mitigation off. This had the effect of gutting the class in every single area of play. Soloing went away, group desirability went away, and pull survivability went away. The irony? Those 'uber' monks who had that unbalanced gear didn't feel it much at all, and they were the ones VI was aiming at.<br>
<br>
Needless to say, this made a lot of monks sad. Then angry. Then livid. After a lot of accounts poofing, and a lot of vitriol the devs finally got a_clue01, and are going to look into the nerf.<br>
<br>
Having said all that, I still play my monk as primary, simply due to time invested, getting to 60+ on a second char is hard (read: time consuming), and monks are still decent at DPS. The new POP AAs have changed the endgame landscape quite visibly. With full AAs and one of the end game 2hbs monks are once again topping archers for total DPS. This has been parsed by FOH's premier ranger Sean. With raid buffs and full AAs Sean was barely topping 200DPS sustained, while a monk without full AAs was sustaining 214DPS. <p>See me at: <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=47953">Schezarine's Sexay Stuff</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
See my BST: <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105950">Schezanna's Savage Suite</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
---<br>
I *am* the Chinpokomon master!</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showMessageRange?topicID=8028.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showMessageRange?topicID=8028.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showMessageRange?topicID=8028.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a> <b>4</b> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showMessageRange?topicID=8028.topic&start=81&stop=81>5</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showPrevMessage?topicID=8028.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showNextMessage?topicID=8028.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.threadControl?topicID=8028.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=8028.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=8028.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="themagicianstowergeneral">General<option value="themagicianstowerfrm32">Class Balance<option value="themagicianstowerfrm45">User Interface<opt